---json
{
  "layout": "layouts/t-money.njk",
  "permalink": "/quickbooks/cleanup/",
  "slug": "cleanup",
  "tierClass": "section--tier-bofu",
  "bodyClass": "page--bofu",
  "title": "QuickBooks File Cleanup by Certified ProAdvisors · TechBrot",
  "description": "Independent QuickBooks file cleanup by Certified ProAdvisors — fix broken bank feeds, file corruption, reconciliation discrepancies, multi-user issues, and version mismatches. Fixed-fee scope, delivered by vetted local operators.",
  "breadcrumb": [
    { "name": "Home", "href": "/" },
    { "name": "QuickBooks", "href": "/quickbooks/" },
    { "name": "File cleanup" }
  ],
  "hero": {
    "eyebrow": "QuickBooks file cleanup",
    "heading": "When QuickBooks itself is the problem.",
    "subheading": "Broken bank feeds. File corruption. Reconciliation that won&rsquo;t balance. Multi-user errors. Version conflicts. TechBrot Certified ProAdvisors repair the file, restore the data, and document every fix &mdash; independent expertise that goes beyond what Intuit product support provides.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=qb-cleanup", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Get the free file review", "href": "/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review", "class": "btn--ghost" },
      { "label": "Speak to a ProAdvisor", "tel": true, "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  },
  "inBrief": {
    "text": "<strong>QuickBooks file cleanup</strong> is a project-based engagement to repair file-level issues and restore data integrity inside your company file &mdash; bank-feed reconnection, reconciliation rebuild, undeposited-funds clearing, duplicate/missing-transaction resolution, corruption recovery, multi-user repair, and version-conflict resolution &mdash; by Certified ProAdvisors across Online, Desktop, Enterprise, and Payroll. Fixed fee <strong>$1,200&ndash;$12,000+</strong>, typically 1&ndash;4 weeks.",
    "source": "Distinct from bookkeeping cleanup (financial reconstruction) and migration. Not affiliated with Intuit Inc."
  },
  "ctaBand": {
    "eyebrow": "File cleanup starts here",
    "heading": "Let&rsquo;s see what your file actually needs.",
    "lede": "Book a free 30-minute file diagnostic. We&rsquo;ll review your QuickBooks file, identify the data-integrity issues, and deliver a written fixed-fee scope within 3 business days &mdash; before any work begins.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=qb-cleanup", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Get the free file review", "href": "/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  }
}
---

<section class="section section--compact" id="cleanup-proof">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="proof-strip">
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>4&times;</b> Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>Data-integrity</b> file repair</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>Fixed-fee</b> written scope, first</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>1 business day</b> response</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><span class="proof-strip__rating">5.0</span> 2 verified Clutch reviews</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact" id="cleanup-credentials">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Certified by Intuit</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor credentials.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Every TechBrot operator holds active Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor credentials across the full QuickBooks stack, plus the Intuit Certified Bookkeeping Professional credential. Verification available on request.</p>
    </header>
    <ul class="checks-list">
      {%- for c in credentials %}<li>{{ c | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="cleanup-definition">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The engagement</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What QuickBooks cleanup actually is.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>QuickBooks file cleanup is a project-based engagement to repair file-level issues and restore data integrity inside a QuickBooks company file. It covers bank-feed reconnection, reconciliation rebuild, undeposited-funds clearing, duplicate-transaction resolution, missing-transaction reconstruction, multi-user mode repairs, version-conflict resolution, file-corruption recovery, and chart-of-accounts restructuring &mdash; delivered by Certified ProAdvisors across QuickBooks Online, Desktop, Enterprise, and Payroll. Most engagements complete in 1&ndash;4 weeks at a fixed fee against a written scope.</p>
      <p>Left alone, file issues exhibit <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/cleanup-bookkeeping/?intent=cleanup">compounding reconciliation drift</a> &mdash; a broken feed or unresolved discrepancy carries into the next period and the gap grows until the file won&rsquo;t close. File cleanup is distinct from <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/cleanup-bookkeeping/?intent=cleanup">bookkeeping cleanup</a> (broader financial reconstruction) and from <a href="/quickbooks/migration/?intent=quickbooks-migration">QuickBooks migration</a> (Desktop-to-Online or software-switch work).</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="cleanup-signals">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Is it time?</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">If you&rsquo;ve hit any of these, you need a ProAdvisor.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for s in signals %}
      <div class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__opener">{{ s.opener | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="cleanup-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">QuickBooks cleanup, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="cleanup-deliverables">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The scope</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What QuickBooks cleanup actually delivers.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for d in deliverables %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <p class="num">{{ d.num }}</p>
        <h3>{{ d.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ d.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="cleanup-process">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The process</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">From file diagnostic to clean QuickBooks.</h2>
    </header>
    <ol class="process-diagram">
      {%- for s in process %}
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">{{ s.num }}</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">{{ s.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
        <p class="process-step__body"><strong>{{ s.when | safe }}</strong></p>
      </li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="cleanup-compare">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The difference</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What changes when the file is clean.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Cleanup unwinds the file-level <strong>compounding reconciliation drift</strong> &mdash; here is the before and after, dimension by dimension.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="vs-scroll">
      <table class="vs-table">
        <caption class="sr-only">A QuickBooks file before and after a TechBrot cleanup, by dimension.</caption>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th scope="col">Dimension</th>
            <th scope="col">Before cleanup</th>
            <th scope="col" class="vs-table__us">After cleanup</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {%- for row in compare %}
          <tr>
            <th scope="row">{{ row.dim | safe }}</th>
            <td class="vs-table__concede">{{ row.before | safe }}</td>
            <td class="vs-table__us"><strong>{{ row.after | safe }}</strong></td>
          </tr>
          {%- endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="cleanup-pricing">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Pricing</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Fixed fee, written scope, no hourly billing.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Three tiers; ranges are typical, final pricing follows the diagnostic. If your cleanup also needs bookkeeping reconstruction across prior periods, see <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/cleanup-bookkeeping/?intent=cleanup">bookkeeping cleanup</a> &mdash; the engagements pair seamlessly.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for t in tiers %}
      <article class="review-card">
        {%- if t.note %}<p class="review-card__role">{{ t.note | safe }}</p>{%- endif %}
        <h3>{{ t.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact"><strong>{{ t.price | safe }}</strong></p>
        <p class="review-card__fact"><strong>For:</strong> {{ t.forWhom | safe }}</p>
        <ul class="checks-list">
          {%- for b in t.bullets %}<li>{{ b | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
        </ul>
        <a class="review-card__link" href="/contact/?intent=qb-cleanup">{{ t.cta | safe }} <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="cleanup-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who performs the work</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A named Certified ProAdvisor. Not an offshore call center.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Every TechBrot QuickBooks cleanup is delivered by a vetted local operator &mdash; an independent accounting practice running under TechBrot&rsquo;s brand, standards, and infrastructure. Every operator holds active QuickBooks ProAdvisor certifications across Online, Desktop, Enterprise, and Payroll. Platform-level quality review backs every engagement, and if continuity is ever a question, the platform handles the transition without losing file context.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="cleanup-next">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Around the cleanup</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">File cleanup is often part of a larger engagement.</h2>
    </header>
    {%- for n in nextSteps %}
    <div class="stack-8">
      <h3><a href="{{ n.href }}">{{ n.title | safe }}</a></h3>
      <p class="prose">{{ n.body | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="cleanup-intake">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Start now</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Scope your QuickBooks cleanup.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Tell us the basics and a Certified ProAdvisor replies within one business day with a written fixed-fee scope. Prefer the full intake? The <a href="/contact/?intent=qb-cleanup">complete contact form</a> captures every detail.</p>
    </header>
    {%- set intakePrefix = "qbc" %}
    {%- set intakeFormId = "cleanup-intake-form" %}
    {%- set intakeIntent = "qb-cleanup" %}
    {%- set intakeSourceType = "bofu-conversion" %}
    {%- set intakeFunnelStage = "BOFU" %}
    {%- set intakeLegend = "What we should look at" %}
    {%- set intakeNote = "QuickBooks cleanup is the common reason businesses reach this page &mdash; add anything else you want scoped in the same call." %}
    {%- set intakeConsent = "I agree to be contacted by TechBrot regarding this QuickBooks cleanup inquiry." %}
    {%- set intakeSubmit = "Send the Discovery Brief" %}
    {%- set intakeReassurance = "No spam, no list, no obligation. A Certified ProAdvisor replies within one business day." %}
    {% include "partials/intake-form.njk" %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="cleanup-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Common questions</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What people ask before scoping a QuickBooks cleanup.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="cleanup-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="cleanup-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
